#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:5
msgid "Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:7
msgid ""
"This document describes the general project guidelines that apply to nova-"
"core and nova-drm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:11
msgid "Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:13
msgid ""
"The Nova project uses the Rust programming language. In this context, all "
"rules of the Rust for Linux project as documented in :doc:`../../rust/"
"general-information` apply. Additionally, the following rules apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:18
msgid ""
"Unless technically necessary otherwise (e.g. uAPI), any driver code is "
"written in Rust."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:21
msgid ""
"Unless technically necessary, unsafe Rust code must be avoided. In case of "
"technical necessity, unsafe code should be isolated in a separate component "
"providing a safe API for other driver code to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:26
msgid "Style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:28
msgid ""
"All rules of the Rust for Linux project as documented in :doc:`../../rust/"
"coding-guidelines` apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:31
msgid ""
"For a submit checklist, please also see the `Rust for Linux Submit checklist "
"addendum <https://rust-for-linux.com/contributing#submit-checklist-"
"addendum>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:35
msgid "Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:37
msgid ""
"The availability of proper documentation is essential in terms of "
"scalability, accessibility for new contributors and maintainability of a "
"project in general, but especially for a driver running as complex hardware "
"as Nova is targeting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:41
msgid ""
"Hence, adding documentation of any kind is very much encouraged by the "
"project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:43
msgid "Besides that, there are some minimum requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:45
msgid ""
"Every non-private structure needs at least a brief doc comment explaining "
"the semantical sense of the structure, as well as potential locking and "
"lifetime requirements. It is encouraged to have the same minimum "
"documentation for non-trivial private structures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:50
msgid ""
"uAPIs must be fully documented with kernel-doc comments; additionally, the "
"semantical behavior must be explained including potential special or corner "
"cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:54
msgid ""
"The APIs connecting the 1st level driver (nova-core) with 2nd level drivers "
"must be fully documented. This includes doc comments, potential locking and "
"lifetime requirements, as well as example code if applicable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:58
msgid ""
"Abbreviations must be explained when introduced; terminology must be "
"uniquely defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:61
msgid ""
"Register addresses, layouts, shift values and masks must be defined "
"properly; unless obvious, the semantical sense must be documented. This only "
"applies if the author is able to obtain the corresponding information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:66
msgid "Acceptance Criteria"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/nova/guidelines.rst:68
msgid ""
"Patches must only be applied if reviewed by at least one other person on the "
"mailing list; this also applies for maintainers."
msgstr ""
